<title>The Mantis, his wife and their things</title>
<summary><i>... an explanation that the Moon has the power of talking, because he belongs to the Mantis, all of whose things talk (L II.-6. 670-677). </i>|kaggen<i> </i>(the Mantis) speaks to the Moon because he has created the Moon from his shoe, which can speak. All of |kaggen&apos;s things can speak and have &apos;understanding&apos;, as do those belonging to his wife, |huntu !kat !katten.</summary><comments>1) p.669v: a note by ||kabbo on death; see <i>//kabbo tells of death, the hole, and the path of the First Bushmen </i>(pp.669v-670v), 2) This story is found in Book II-6</comments><date>October 1871</date><storypages>670-678</storypages><category>|kaggen (the Mantis)</category><category>Celestial bodies and aeroscopy</category><author>||kabbo (Jantje) (II)</author><keyword><kw>|kaggen</kw><subkw>the Mantis</subkw></keyword>
